Alright, let me start off with the basics. First, and foremost, we can be ranged tankers or ranged damage dealers, But one of the most crucial things I have found in the Commando is BLOCK VALUE. Commandos are intended for blocking, rather than dodging, evading, parry, etc. BLOCK CHANCE increases the chance you'll be able to block something, where BLOCK VALUE increases the amount of damage reduced.
Now since we don't exactly have a great amount of constitution like Jedi in some heroic instances, it would be wise to stack some Constitution.Further more, since Commando is really the only profession that isn't picky about armor types, you can wear any armor. Assault, Recon, Battle it's all a personal choice.
But the Battle armor is recommended primus layered 6600 Kin 6600 En 5400 all it is the best armor for a mando because you can grab a 1500 kin 1500 En Ent buff or a 2250 En 2250 Kin 7% glancing blow 6% second chance, precision, luck and constitution depends on what you will be doing and what suit you're wearing.
The armor caps on 10 kin and 10k En but running with 11k+ on both wont hurt But it has been discussed several times and confirmated by several class senators than running with more than 10k 10k its a waste also don't forget that commandos have 1k innate armor to both Kin and En.
A nice little thing to do for your armor is ( SEAS ) also called 35s
If you're going for a block suit it's recommended that you stack Precision, Strength and constitution OR perc cons agi for the Basic Armor Attachments. For the Exotic Attachments Critical hit reduction, Healing potency, Heavy weapon damage
If you're going for a DPS (Damage Per Second) PVP / PVE it's recommended that you stack Constitution, Precision, Luck a chance to deal a critical. For the exotic attachements Devastation, Heavy weapon damage, Heavy Weapon critical.
If you are in the beginning and you have no money for devastation mods u can switch them for pvp critical.
also this will help u allot to understand how and what are the benefits from the stats

GCWCity invasions now check to see if the general is alive and completes the invasion if the general has died, but did not notify the server.A final communication from an Imperial or Rebel leader will congratulate faction and faction helper players that participated in a successful defense of a GCW city or killing the General.Invasions will run concurrently in all three cities.System messages for repairing or missing tools should not be sent on a menu request any longer for barricades and patrol objects. FAME- is comprised of some of the oldest members in Galaxies. FAME was founded out of the unification of SoR (formerly OmNi, which also splintered into the legendary holocron farmers of HUG) and FWO, neighboring guilds in the city of Freedom on Lok. Many people have come and gone, and a many of those have made their mark on the group forever. Some have been around since the very first day the servers went live, while others have been active only a few months. FAME- is the kind of group where, if you want it, you can do it, and we'll get you there. And more than likely, it will be quite a ride.
FAME has made large investments into reverse engineering of ship parts to build elite PVP squadrons. Additionally, the guild has tapped its resources to put together two different kinds of uniform FAME armor suits for tactical missions (more pvp!). It's a strong group, and it's a friendly group. It's also a rebel group. We don't have a lot of rules, but those we do have we adhere very strictly. At the end of the day, we've spent a lot of time building ourselves into a group that is as much a family as possible.
The members of FAME would like the Galaxy to know that, since 2003, they have had at least one person in the armed services deployed somewhere nasty. Right now, our dear friend Betha (a big goofy lizard, incredible pilot, and very good friend) is tromping around the sand of Iraq. We miss him, and we have our fingers (furry, scaley, or otherwise) crossed for his safe return.
